    <dashboard name='Smartphone Market Analysis: Overview, Deep Dive &amp; Strategic Insights' type='storyboard'>
      <style>
        <style-rule element='story-title'>
          <format attr='text-align' value='center' />
        </style-rule>
      </style>
      <size sizing-mode='automatic' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='2' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98002' id='1' param='vert' removable='false' type-v2='layout-flow' w='99018' x='491' y='999'>
            <zone h='5243' id='3' type-v2='title' w='99018' x='491' y='999' />
            <zone h='12609' id='4' is-fixed='true' paired-zone-id='5' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard-nav' w='99018' x='491' y='6242' />
            <zone h='80150' id='5' paired-zone-id='4' removable='false' type-v2='flipboard' w='99018' x='491' y='18851'>
              <flipboard active-id='2' nav-type='caption' show-nav-arrows='true'>
                <story-points>
                  <story-point caption='Android dominates the OS market, while Apple and Samsung lead premium pricing. Mid-range brands like Xiaomi and Motorola deliver strong performance at lower prices. This sets the baseline market structure.' captured-sheet='Market Overview' id='2' />
                  <story-point caption='Top-rated models span both premium and budget phones. RAM generally drives performance, but efficient models like Pixel 6a show strong results with moderate specifications. This highlights consumer value choices.' captured-sheet='Consumer Insights' id='1' />
                  <story-point caption='A few brands (Samsung, Apple) drive most revenue, while competitors like Xiaomi and Motorola add significant value volume to the Market. This shows where to focus the portfolio and margin strategies.' captured-sheet='Parento Analysis of Brand Contribution' id='3' />
                  <story-point caption='Brands are clearly tiered: Premium (Apple, Samsung, Sony), Mid-range (OnePlus, Google, Oppo), and Budget (Motorola, Xiaomi, Vivo). This supports differentiated pricing and marketing strategies.' captured-sheet='Average Price Per Brand' id='4' />
                  <story-point caption='Younger buyers gravitate toward mid-range models, while older age consumers spend more on premium devices. This aligns product recommendations with affordability and lifecycle.' captured-sheet='Age Group VS Price' id='5' />
                  <story-point caption='Brand dominance varies by City: Samsung and OnePlus lead in tech Cities, while Xiaomi and Motorola are strong in value-driven markets. Regional campaigns should reflect these differences.' captured-sheet='Brand Preference By Gender' id='6' />
                  <story-point caption='Action Plan:&#10;- Defend premium margins with Apple/Samsung.&#10;- Promote value leaders like Xiaomi/Motorola.&#10;- Match product tiers to age and salary segments.&#10;- Tailor campaigns by regional brand strength.&#10;' captured-sheet='' id='7' />
                </story-points>
              </flipboard>
            </zone>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <simple-id uuid='{8F91672F-1272-4801-A4C9-F9307DA698D0}' />
    </dashboard>
